msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:18-1
msgid "Research It On the Fly"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-2
msgid ""
"To quickly lookup an item of interest using Research It, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:21-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>.<br /> The "
"Research It dialog box appears with focus in the Word or Phrase edit combo "
"box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:23-4
msgid "Do one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:26-4
msgid ""
"Type a word, phrase, date, tracking number, or other item into the edit "
"combo box, press <strong>TAB</strong>, and then select a lookup source from "
"the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:27-4
msgid ""
"Select an item from the edit combo box history list, press <strong>TAB</"
"strong>, and then select a lookup source from the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:28-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to jump directly to the Lookup Source list, and "
"then select a lookup source. (This option is useful when using a news lookup "
"source.)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:31-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>ENTER</strong>.<br /> After a few seconds, the JAWS Results "
"Viewer window opens and displays the search results. <br /> <br /> "
"<strong>Note: </strong> For specific examples describing how to enter search "
"parameters, refer to <a href=\"#ResearchItExamples\">Research It Examples</"
"a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:37-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.h2:37-1"
msgid "Keystrokes"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:38-2
msgid ""
"The following briefly describes the available Research It keystrokes. Note "
"that if JAWS is configured for Laptop Layout mode, substitute <strong>CAPS "
"LOCK</strong> for the <strong>INSERT</strong> key."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:40-4
msgid ""
"<strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>: Opens the Research It "
"dialog box, where you can then type a word or expression of interest, and "
"then select a lookup source to perform your search. For example, this can be "
"a word to use with the Wikipedia search query to view its meaning or "
"description. This convenient, layered keystroke provides the most efficient "
"way to search for a term. <strong>Note:</strong> When using this keystroke, "
"press and release <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, and then press "
"<strong>R</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:41-4
msgid ""
"<strong>INSERT+WINDOWS Key+R</strong>: Launches Research It and uses the "
"primary lookup source to directly show results in the Results Viewer. This "
"keystroke bypasses the Research It dialog box.<br /> <br /> By default, "
"Wiktionary is the primary lookup source. This means that while the cursor is "
"on a word in a document or Web page, you can press this keystroke and "
"quickly lookup the Wiktionary description for that word. You can always "
"change the primary lookup source at any time using the <a "
"href=\"#Default\">Options button</a> or the JAWS Settings Center, which lets "
"you select which lookup source to use as the default. As you become more "
"familiar with Research It, you will want to change the default lookup source "
"used by JAWS, or just use a different lookup source on the fly."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:44-4
msgid ""
"<strong>INSERT+CTRL+WINDOWS Key+R</strong>: Functions the same as the "
"<strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong> keystroke."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:45-4
msgid ""
"<strong>INSERT+F2</strong>, <strong>R</strong>: Opens Research It from the "
"Run JAWS Manager dialog box. It provides another way for you to select a "
"lookup source for the word at the current cursor location. Note that this is "
"temporary and does not change your default settings. JAWS will continue to "
"use the primary lookup source the next time you run Research It."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:46-4
msgid ""
"<strong>ESC</strong>: Closes the Results Viewer window and returns to your "
"original focus point."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:48-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.h2:48-1"
msgid "Lookup Sources"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:49-2
msgid "JAWS comes with the following lookup sources."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:51-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Wiktionary</strong>: Provides a dictionary description of the word "
"at the current cursor location in a document or Web page. You can also use "
"the edit combo box to type a word to lookup. Wiktionary is the primary "
"lookup source. Refer to the <a href=\"#WiktionaryExample\">Wiktionary "
"example</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:52-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Wikipedia</strong>: Provides encyclopedia results for the word at "
"the current cursor location in a document or Web page. You can also use the "
"edit combo box to type a word to lookup. See the <a "
"href=\"#WikipediaExample\">Wikipedia example</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:53-4
msgid ""
"<strong>BBC Top News Stories</strong>: Displays a link and a synopsis of "
"news stories as reported by the BBC. Select the link to read the complete "
"story. See the <a href=\"#NewsExample\">News Stories example</a> to help you "
"configure the news search."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:54-4
msgid ""
"<strong>CNN Headline News</strong>: Displays a link and a synopsis of news "
"stories as reported by CNN Headline News. Select the link to read the "
"complete story. To use this lookup source, leave the edit combo box blank, "
"and then select it from the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:55-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Fox News Stories</strong>: Displays a link and a synopsis of news "
"stories as reported by Fox News. Select the link to read the complete story. "
"To use this lookup source, leave the edit combo box blank, and then select "
"it from the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:56-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Technology News from CNET</strong>: Displays a link and a synopsis "
"of the latest headlines from CNET news. Select the link to read the complete "
"story. To use this lookup source, leave the edit combo box blank, and then "
"select it from the list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:57-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Bookshare™ Book Search</strong>: Displays search results from "
"Bookshare.org based on an author’s name, a book’s ISBN number, or words "
"found in a book title or book description. If a match is found, the result "
"appears as a link containing the author, title, and copyright date."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:58-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Area Code Lookup</strong>: Type a U.S. or Canadian area code into "
"the edit combo box to learn the city, state, or province location for that "
"area code."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:59-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Time Search</strong>: Displays the current time and time zone for "
"any location typed into the edit field. <strong>Note:</strong> Be specific "
"when entering a location since one name may represent multiple cities. For "
"example, if you only type London into the edit combo box, you will receive "
"time results for London, England, U.K., London, Ontario, Canada, and London, "
"Arkansas, U.S.A. If no result is returned, enter another city that is close "
"to the preferred location."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:60-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Convert Currency</strong>: Use this lookup source to convert an "
"amount of money from one currency into a foreign equivalent. The current "
"day’s exchange rate is used to convert the currency values typed into the "
"lookup edit field. Refer to the <a href=\"#CurrencyExample\">Convert "
"Currency example</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:61-4
msgid ""
"<strong>Flight Info Lookup</strong>: Provides recent or current flight "
"status when you type an airline abbreviation followed by a valid flight "
"number in the edit combo box. Two letter abbreviations are used to identify "
"an airline. A list of abbreviations will appear in the Results Viewer if you "
"enter an invalid airline code, an invalid flight number, or no information "
"in the edit combo box. Text typed in the edit combo box is not case-"
"sensitive and can be entered with or without a space between the airline "
"abbreviation and flight number."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:63-1
msgid ""
"If you are a software developer or script developer, you can create and "
"customize your own lookup module and tailor it to your organization's needs. "
"A law or medical office can have a search engine for legal and medical "
"terms, while a school or government agency can have a lookup module "
"dedicated to specific acronyms and terminology. Visit the <a href=\"https://"
"support.freedomscientific.com/Products/Blindness/JawsDocumentation\" "
"target=\"_blank\">JAWS Documentation Web page</a> to download a developer's "
"guide that outlines formatting for rule sets and debugging techniques."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:64-1
msgid "Research It Examples"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:65-2
msgid ""
"There are several ways to run Research It. You can use the default lookup "
"source, or you can select a lookup source from the Research It list. The "
"following examples show different ways to search for specific information. "
"For other ideas and ways to use Research It, listen to the <a href=\"https://"
"www.freedomscientific.com/About/FSCast/FullListing#Episode33\" "
"target=\"_blank\">August 2009 FSCast</a> for a demonstration."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:66-2
msgid "Wiktionary"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:67-2
msgid ""
"Imagine that you are reading a document online and you come across an "
"unfamiliar word. With Wiktionary set as your primary lookup source, you can "
"do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:69-4
msgid ""
"While the cursor is on that word, press <strong>INSERT+WINDOWS Key+R</"
"strong> to launch Research It.<br /> <br /> After a few seconds, the JAWS "
"Results Viewer window opens and displays a Wiktionary-based description of "
"the word. With the Results Viewer open, you can also select and copy the "
"information to the Windows clipboard."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:72-4
msgid ""
"After reading the description, press <strong>ESC</strong> to close the "
"Results Viewer, and JAWS returns to the cursor location in your document."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:74-2
msgid "Wikipedia"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:75-2
msgid "You can use Wikipedia to quickly research an item."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:77-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:77-4"
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:78-4
msgid ""
"In the edit combo box, type the term that you want to find, and then press "
"<strong>TAB</strong>. For example, type:<br /> <br /> <strong> Freedom "
"Scientific</strong>, and press <strong>TAB</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:82-4
msgid ""
"Use the <strong>UP</strong> and <strong>DOWN ARROWS</strong> or first letter "
"navigation to select Wikipedia, and press <strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:83-4
msgid ""
"After a few seconds, the Results Viewer window opens and displays the "
"results returned from the Wikipedia lookup. Press <strong>ESC</strong> to "
"close the Results Viewer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:85-2
msgid "News Stories"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:86-2
msgid ""
"For a summary of current news stories, you can use the following procedure "
"for the BBC, CNN, Fox News, and Technology News for CNET lookup sources."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:88-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>, and then press "
"<strong>TAB</strong> to move focus to the Lookup Source list."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:89-4
msgid ""
"Select a news lookup source from the list, and press <strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:90-4
msgid ""
"After a few seconds, the Results Viewer window opens and displays a synopsis "
"of news stories using the selected lookup source. If you want more "
"information about a specific story, select its Full Article link. This "
"action closes the Results Viewer window and then displays the complete story "
"in a Web browser. Otherwise, press <strong>ESC</strong> to close the Results "
"Viewer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:92-1
msgid "Convert Currency"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:93-2
msgid ""
"Use the Convert Currency lookup source to quickly convert an amount of money "
"from one currency to another currency. The lookup source uses three-"
"character abbreviations to represent <a "
"href=\"Currency_Abbreviations.htm\">international currencies</a>. The "
"conversion that appears is based on the day’s current conversion rate."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:95-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:95-4"
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:96-4
msgid ""
"Type the amount of money and currency that you want to convert from followed "
"by the currency that you want to convert to, and then press <strong>TAB</"
"strong>. For example, to convert 100 U.S. dollars into Euros, type:<br /> "
"<br /> <strong>100 USD EUR</strong> and then press<strong> TAB</strong>.<br /"
"> <br /> <strong>Note:</strong> Make sure to include a space between each "
"item. Always use the currency’s three-character abbreviation. Select <a "
"href=\"Currency_Abbreviations.htm\">currency abbreviations</a> for a list of "
"currencies."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:102-4
msgid ""
"Use the <strong>UP</strong> and <strong>DOWN ARROWS</strong> or first letter "
"navigation to select Convert Currency and then press <strong>ENTER</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:103-4
msgid ""
"After a few seconds, the Results Viewer window opens and displays the "
"conversion results, for example:<br /> <br /> <strong>100 U.S. dollars = "
"67.4399784 Euros</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:107-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.h2:107-1"
msgid "Changing the Default Lookup Source"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:108-2
msgid ""
"The fastest way to change the default lookup source is through the Research "
"It dialog box as described in the following steps. Note that the default can "
"also be set using the <a href=\"#SC\">Settings Center</a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:110-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:110-4"
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>. The Research It "
"dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:111-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Options button, and then press "
"<strong>ENTER</strong>. The Research It Options dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:112-4
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:112-4"
msgid ""
"Press the <strong>UP</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROWS</strong> to select a "
"lookup source, and then press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Set "
"Primary button."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:113-4
msgid ""
"Press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to make the selected item the primary lookup "
"source, and then choose OK to save changes and close the Research It Options "
"dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:115-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> After setting a default lookup source, you can use "
"<strong>INSERT+WINDOWS Key+R</strong>, which bypasses the Research It dialog "
"box and automatically launches the Results Viewer using the new default. You "
"can also continue to use <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</"
"strong> to run Research It."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:116-1
msgid "Using Settings Center"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:117-1
msgid ""
"To assign a default lookup source using Settings Center, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:119-3
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+F2</strong>, and select Settings Center."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:120-8
msgid "Press <strong>CTRL+SHIFT+D</strong> to load the JAWS default settings."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:122-8
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the tree view, and then select and "
"open the Research It group."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:123-8
msgid ""
"Press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to choose the Configure Lookup button. The "
"Research It Options dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:124-8
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:124-8"
msgid ""
"Press the <strong>UP</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROWS</strong> to select a "
"lookup source, and then press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Set "
"Primary button."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:125-8
msgid ""
"Press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to make the selected item the primary lookup "
"source."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:126-8
msgid "Choose OK to save changes and close the Research It Options dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:127-8
msgid "Choose OK to save changes and close Settings Center."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:129-1
msgid ""
"Select <a href=\"SettingsCenter.chm::/ResearchIt/"
"Research_It_Options_Dialog.htm\">Research It Options Dialog</a> for more "
"information about this dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:130-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.h2:130-1"
msgid "Removing or Adding a Lookup Source"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:131-1
msgid "To remove or add an item to the Lookup Source list, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:133-3
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\Research_It.htm+html.body.ol.li:133-3"
msgid ""
"Press <strong>INSERT+SPACEBAR</strong>, <strong>R</strong>. The Research It "
"dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:135-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the Options button, and then press "
"<strong>SPACEBAR</strong>. The Research It Options dialog box opens."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:136-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>UP</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROWS</strong> to select a lookup "
"source, and then do one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:140-3
msgid ""
"To remove a lookup source from the list, press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to "
"clear the check box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:141-3
msgid ""
"To add a lookup source to the list, press <strong>SPACEBAR</strong> to "
"select the check box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CResearch_It.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:144-3
msgid ""
"Press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to the <strong>OK</strong> button and "
"then press <strong>ENTER</strong>. <br /> <br /> <strong>Note:</strong> When "
"you update your copy of JAWS, all lookup sources are restored and appear in "
"the list box."
msgstr ""

